          "Authors create a 5-stage logistic regression to predict succes at next assignment in 5 different stages of course completion: Week 2, Week 4, Week 6, Week 7, Week 10.\n\nOverall, the models created seem to be especially effective at Stage 3: week 6. \n\nDifferent features are important at different stages.",
          "No model assessment strategy → Data leakage issues.\n\nNo algorithms tested beyond Logistic Regression.\n\nSome questionable preprocessing decisions: Pearson correlation and Label Encoding for non-ordinal variables."
